            <thetext>The qx.lang.String.capitalize() method is buggy, as it cannot handle correctly strings with non-ASCII caracters (eg: german characters with umlaut)

How to reporoduce: 

    var cityName = qx.lang.String.capitalize(&quot;bahnhof zimmernsupra-töttelstädt&quot;);
    console.log(cityName);

Expected result: Bahnhof Zimmernsupra-Töttelstädt
Actual result: Bahnhof Zimmernsupra-TöTtelstäDt

(notice the capitalized T and D inside TöTtelstäDt)</thetext>
